$interpreted: Local: Amazing! Thanks so much, good sir! You're a real knight in shining armor! They ran away scared after seeing how powerful you are!
Pang: Please, please. It was nothing, really. Not worth mentioning. Since the issue has been resolved, I shall take my leave.
Local: Hey, hey, hey! No need to speed away, good sir. We still haven't repaid you.
Pang: No, I'm just a mere traveler. I wouldn't want to cause you any inconvenience by overstaying my welcome...
Jia-Shen: Meemaw...
Granny Xica: ...I'm not moving away from here, but I won't force you to stay here and take this risk with me.
Granny Xica: You...ought to go...
Jia-Shen: I...
Local: Granny Xica, don't pay attention to that cowardly traitor!
Child: Yeah! Why don't you stick your head in that shell and get the heck outta here! This tiger hero is all we need!
Jia-Shen: (Yeah, this is the way is oughta be. There's no use for me there anymore.)
Jia-Shen: (As long as that tiger fellar's there, Humpty probably won't tear down the houses...)
？？？: If you leave, what's Granny Xica going to do?
Jia-Shen: What are you doing here?
Pang: Granny Xica sent me to find you. You were just trying to help, why didn't you explain your position more clearly?
Pang: Walking away from a problem won't fix anything.
Jia-Shen: What's there to say? I'm just a gosh darn coward, that's all. Even if that's true, there's no way I can protect Meemaw's home!
Jia-Shen: I'm clear as the blue sky on what kinda no good, good for nothing I am. They've got you now, and that's enough.
Jia-Shen: They don't need a tortoise that doesn't have the guts to face reality.
Pang: Don't speak of yourself like that. Everyone has value.
Jia-Shen: Value? What value? The funny guy, huh? Just here to put on a show, huh? To be bullied? I ain't good for nothin' but a stinkin' laugh! HA! HA! HA!
Pang: You're drunk. Put down the booze.
Jia-Shen: Typical. You elite tigers, don't know what it FEELS like to have to pander to others whims 'n fancies~ Must be nice. Everyone loving you and all~
Pang: ...Come with me.
Jia-Shen: I. Don't. WANNA! You don't know what it feels like to have to act meek and subservient all the time, how much suffering I endure!!!
Pang: You finished?
Jia-Shen: I...I'm sorry...
Pang: Nobody is perfect. Everyone makes mistakes. I know how you feel.
Pang: Come on. They're all waiting for you.
Jia-Shen: But...they already hate me...
Pang: You'll never know until you see it with you're own eyes. At the very least, there's one person who doesn't feel that way.
Jia-Shen: You...why do you insist on helping me?
Pang: ...I envy you greatly. At least you have someone who awaits your return.
